          <div class="definition-box">
            <p>Ajax and Pickering are part of Durham Region's rapidly growing east GTA — a corridor where Chinese-Canadian families have been settling in increasing numbers. Family law cases here reflect east GTA's specific character: <strong>rising property values, growing families with grandparent involvement in childcare, and a shortage of Mandarin-speaking family lawyers</strong> in the area. Miao He (何淼) fills that gap, providing full Mandarin family law services to Ajax and Pickering clients. Zoom consultations available. LSO #83315K.</p>
          </div>

          <h2>Family Law Services for Ajax and Pickering Chinese-Canadian Families</h2>
          <p>Ajax and Pickering clients often face the same core family law issues as the rest of the GTA — but with less access to Mandarin-speaking legal help. Miao He brings the same depth of service to east GTA clients that GTA-core communities have access to, with the convenience of phone and Zoom consultations.</p>

          <h3>Separation Agreements: Resolving Everything Before Court</h3>
          <p>A Separation Agreement is a legally binding contract that resolves property division, support obligations, and parenting arrangements between separating spouses — without going to court. For Ajax and Pickering families where both parties are willing to negotiate, a well-drafted Separation Agreement is the most efficient path to resolution. It eliminates uncertainty, reduces legal costs, and can be incorporated into a divorce order. Miao He drafts Separation Agreements in Mandarin and English, explaining every provision clearly before signing.</p>

          <h3>Property Division: East GTA Real Estate</h3>
          <p>Property values in Ajax and Pickering have risen significantly over the past decade. When a marriage breaks down, the increase in property value during the marriage is subject to Equalization — but pre-marital value and parental contributions may be excluded. Miao He helps clients establish the correct valuation baseline at the date of marriage and date of separation, protecting assets that should not be split.</p>

          <h3>Child Custody: Grandparent Care and Cultural Arrangements</h3>
          <p>Chinese-Canadian families in Ajax and Pickering frequently rely on grandparents for childcare — a reality that affects custody and parenting time arrangements. Miao He builds Parenting Plans that reflect how these families actually operate: grandparent care time, Chinese school schedules, cultural holiday arrangements, and rules around travel. These specific provisions reduce future disputes by leaving less to interpretation.</p>

          <h3>Child Relocation: When a Spouse Wants to Move</h3>
          <p>If your spouse wants to relocate with the children — to another city, province, or country — this is one of the most serious family law issues you will face. Ontario's Children's Law Reform Act requires notice and either consent or a court order before a custodial parent can relocate a child. Miao He can move urgently to prevent an unauthorized move, and advises clients on relocation rights on both sides of the dispute.</p>

          <div class="qa-block">
            <h3>Q: What is a separation agreement and do I need one?</h3>
            <p>A: A Separation Agreement is a binding contract that resolves property, support, and parenting — without going to court. You don't need one to divorce, but having one makes the process faster and reduces future disputes. Miao He drafts these in Mandarin and English. Call 647-930-6688.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-block">
            <h3>Q: My spouse is talking about moving to another province with our children. Can they do that?</h3>
            <p>A: Not without your consent or a court order. If this is a concern, call 647-930-6688 immediately. Miao He can obtain an urgent court order preventing the move while the matter is resolved properly.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-block">
